state_summary: Tayla Cannon, a sufferer of chronic back pain, started sharing her perspective online about 'proactive' and 'holistic' ways people can get rid of pain. She now has over 130,000 followers on Instagram and has launched a platform called Rebuildr to help rehab professionals run their own businesses online.
evidence: Tayla Cannon moved from Australia to the U.S. for a job in a city she'd never seen before
She started working in physiotherapy, thinking it was helping make a difference in the lives of others
She became disillusioned with the traditional physiotherapy model and shifted her focus to interventional cardiology
keywords: Rebuildr, Tayla Cannon, physiotherapy, chronic back pain, entrepreneurship, startup
